comment.narrative:
Targets for 2020
1.7 Green mortgage mechanism is operated by Qishloq Qurilish Bank (QQB). QQB is expected to issue 528 green mortgages. HACT assessment of 2 more selected financial institutions conducted.
1.8 At least 528 (2,112 people) households accessed the dedicated financial products on low-carbon housing that designed and operated by financial institutions. The proportion of participation by women as green mortgage borrowers should be equal to or greater than the proportion of participation by women in the standard mortgages of the Rural Housing Programme.
1.9 At least 528 (2,112 people) households (20% of women-led households) have access to new rural houses featuring advanced EE/RE technologies;
1.10 Energy audit of at least 60 rural houses conducted to measure energy performance of the EE and low-carbon houses and reflect significant improvements over standard RHP houses;
1.11 Rural technology needs assessment (TNA) conducted and reflects current needs of both men and women;
1.12 At least 10 companies benefited, and volume of their sales increased through supply chain for low-carbon rural housing;
1.13 At least 1 new building code on photovoltaic stations is developed and approved by the Government;
1.16 At least 2 codes on urban-planning/spatial planning are reworked with introduction of energy savings and/or climate considerations 
1.18 At least 90% of project participants (households) are aware of the benefits of EE and LC houses constructed in 2020
1.19 Project communication strategy is tested on women's and men's communication channels in rural areas in 5 more pilot regions.
1.20 IT software system for Monitoring and Evaluation of EE and LC rural houses is developed.
1.21 Project staff and stakeholders are aware of gender issues in project monitoring through shared project and CO monitoring reports.
